@khalibartan So the issue here is that we are doing a `!=` comparison here: https://github.com/pgmpy/pgmpy/blob/dev/pgmpy/factors/JointProbabilityDistribution.py#L171. What I figured is that there is difference in the way python2 and 3 handle this. In case of python2 this statement wasn't even calling Factor's `__eq__` method. Whereas in case of python3 it was called. Here are the docs: https://docs.python.org/2/reference/datamodel.html https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html for both python 2 and 3. 

A simple fix that I figured out was adding `__ne__` method in `Factor`:
```python
    def __ne__(self, other):
        return not self.__eq__(other)
```

Just check if there is a better solution to this.

