@sairamch04 You can adjust the behavior of the pager (less command) to suit your needs. 

Here's how you can change the behavior: https://github.com/dbcli/mssql-cli/blob/master/doc/troubleshooting_guide.md#default-pager-outputs-results-separate-from-main-console

If you uncomment the pager line in your config file it will default to using a sane configuration for the less command. If you just don't want to use a pager at all, you can change that line to say `pager = cat`. That will replace `less` with `cat` which will simply output the results in the same window without paging.

